description.text:
Printing is very simple. Just lay the S Hook flat on the platform and it should build without any problems.
These are the parameters you can adjust:
<b >top_hook_radius</b>: <i >[Mili Meters]</i> This is the inner radius of the top S Hook<br />
<b >top_hook_radius</b> = 33.5;
<b >bottom_hook_radius</b>: <i >[Mili Meters]</i> This is the inner radius of the bottom S Hook<br />
<b >bottom_hook_radius</b> = 7.7;
<b >width</b>: <i >[mili meters]</i> This is the size of the S Hook body (in X&amp;Y directions)<br />
<b >width</b> = 10.0;
<b >thickness</b>: <i >[Milli Meters]</i> This is the thickness of the S Hook (in Z direction)<br />
<b >thickness</b> = 60.0;
<b >start_angle</b>: [DEGREES] This adjusts where the opening in the S Hook starts<br />
<b >start_angle</b> = -10;
<b >end_angle</b>: <i >[DEGREES]</i> This adjusts where the opening of the S Hook ends.
Normally end_angle will be ~-90 degrees. This is so the transition from top to bottom hook is smooth. If you want the opening to be somewhere else than adjust this value.<br />
<b >end_angle</b> = -89;
